of him dying.

03:40.500 --> 03:43.533
I'd have to call his parents
and tell them their son's dead.

03:43.567 --> 03:45.233
And I'm responsible.

03:45.266 --> 03:46.767
[solemn music]

03:47.000 --> 03:48.633
I don't know how
I'd deal with that.

03:48.667 --> 03:51.300
♪ ♪

03:51.333 --> 03:53.200
All right.
Well, go get calmed down.

03:53.233 --> 03:54.400
Make sure everything's
secured back there.

03:54.433 --> 03:56.333
- Yep, my apologies, Cap.

03:56.367 --> 03:58.633
♪ ♪

03:58.667 --> 04:00.600
- I have kids.

04:00.633 --> 04:04.400
And I don't know how
I'd make that call.

04:04.433 --> 04:08.333
♪ ♪

04:08.367 --> 04:10.533
I need a minute.

04:10.567 --> 04:15.333
♪ ♪

04:15.367 --> 04:16.600
- (BLEEP).

04:16.633 --> 04:18.633
- I just heard him
and I turned around.

04:18.667 --> 04:21.333
- What just happened?
- I'm like, "Oh, my God."

04:21.367 --> 04:22.633
- Well, when you're gasping
for breath

04:22.667 --> 04:25.333
and being dragged underwater,
it is forever.

04:25.367 --> 04:27.633
- So, near death experience...

04:27.667 --> 04:28.700
It's scary, man.

04:28.734 --> 04:30.533
- It's so scary.

04:30.567 --> 04:32.300
We don't want people to know
how dangerous the job is,

04:32.333 --> 04:34.433
because that would be scary,
but it is,

04:34.467 --> 04:36.633
and I think Ashton
and what happened today,

04:36.667 --> 04:38.467
is a very good reminder.

04:40.200 --> 04:42.000
- Tender, tender.
Bow deck out to "Seanna."

04:42.033 --> 04:43.400
- Go ahead, "My Seanna."

04:43.433 --> 04:45.333
- Yeah, how you riding
back there?

04:45.367 --> 04:46.700
- I'm all good, Captain.
I'm fine, thank you.

04:46.734 --> 04:48.600
- You okay physically?

04:48.633 --> 04:49.633
- Uh...

04:53.367 --> 04:55.300
- We're gonna get you on board
as quick as we can.

04:55.333 --> 04:57.467
Get your foot elevated,
get some ice on it,

04:57.500 --> 04:59.367
and then the doctor will be
able to see you at 6:00.

05:00.767 --> 05:03.300
- I can't pick the tender up
now, because we're out

05:03.333 --> 05:05.600
in open water and swells
are just too bad

05:05.633 --> 05:07.333
to try and make that pick up.

05:07.367 --> 05:09.767
It's not a pleasant situation,
to say the least.

05:16.266 --> 05:18.467
- Just puts life into
perspective, you know?

05:18.500 --> 05:20.367
It's like, one minute
you're here,

05:20.400 --> 05:22.367
one minute you're gone.

05:22.400 --> 05:23.734
All I'm thinking is,
you know,

05:23.767 --> 05:25.700
I can't wait
to see Ashton.

05:25.734 --> 05:27.400
Give him a hug.

05:27.433 --> 05:29.500
But also, at the same time,
----ing slap him.

05:29.533 --> 05:30.667
Like what the (BLEEP)
were you thinking

05:30.700 --> 05:32.467
stepping over that line?

05:32.500 --> 05:36.033
[exhales deeply]
Sh--.

05:36.066 --> 05:39.033
[upbeat electronic music]

05:39.066 --> 05:45.066
♪ ♪

05:45.100 --> 05:46.600
- What do you think
of our guests' lunch?

05:46.633 --> 05:49.400
- 2:00, so I'm gonna go set
the table now.

05:49.433 --> 05:52.333
- I'm getting hungry.
I like to eat a lot so...

05:52.367 --> 05:54.667
- I do too, that's why I said--

05:56.533 --> 05:58.400
- I enjoy eating.

05:59.500 --> 06:01.633
- I'm king of the world.

06:01.667 --> 06:03.667
- Jimmy, we're about
to have lunch if you're ready.

06:03.700 --> 06:06.533
- Fabulous.
- Definitely.

06:06.567 --> 06:09.567
- As crazy as this morning was,
the show must go on.

06:09.600 --> 06:12.367
These people paid a sh-- ton
of money to be on this boat.

06:12.400 --> 06:14.400
Our job is to distract them
from everything

06:14.433 --> 06:16.467
that went on this morning,
and it starts with lunch.

06:16.500 --> 06:18.500
- Hey, Laura, when you're done
clearing up the crew mess,

06:18.533 --> 06:20.467
you can take
a two-hour break, okay?

06:20.500 --> 06:21.400
- Oh, amazing.
Thanks.

06:21.433 --> 06:23.533
- I love these shape of plates.

06:23.567 --> 06:24.767
- I know, they're so cute.

06:25.000 --> 06:26.400
We should use these more often.

06:26.433 --> 06:28.066
[exciting music]

06:28.100 --> 06:29.667
- Oh, my God.
It looks so good.

06:29.700 --> 06:32.467
