with a red wine reduction,

06:32.500 --> 06:36.100
some turmeric-infused shrimp,
and a little Asian salad.

06:36.133 --> 06:37.433
- Awesome.
- Perfect.

06:37.467 --> 06:38.633
- It looks amazing.
Thank you.

06:38.667 --> 06:40.033
- Enjoy.
- Good job.

06:40.066 --> 06:41.367
- Delicious.
- Mmm.

06:41.400 --> 06:42.767
- You try the shrimp yet?
- Uh-uh.

06:43.000 --> 06:44.633
- It's really good.

06:44.667 --> 06:45.734
- All right, I need somebody
up here on the bow

06:45.767 --> 06:47.400
to get ready to drop the hook.

06:47.433 --> 06:49.333
- Yeah, copy that.
Standing by.

06:49.367 --> 06:51.433
- And drop.

06:56.066 --> 06:57.567
- Five shots at the waterline.

06:59.467 --> 07:01.467
- Ashton, come on alongside.

07:01.500 --> 07:03.033
Let's go you tied up.

07:03.066 --> 07:04.367
- Copy, Cap.

07:04.400 --> 07:07.367
[dramatic music]

07:07.400 --> 07:08.734
♪ ♪

07:08.767 --> 07:10.433
- Okay, you're good.

07:10.467 --> 07:13.066
- Don't ----ing scare me
like that again, bro.

07:13.100 --> 07:14.433
Are you all right?
- Yeah.

07:14.467 --> 07:16.367
- Come here, brother.
- (BLEEP).

07:18.467 --> 07:19.633
- Thanks, dude.
- You all right, babe?

07:19.667 --> 07:21.400
- Don't scare me
like that, bro.

07:21.433 --> 07:22.633
You know not to ----ing
step over that line.

07:22.667 --> 07:24.066
- I know.
- Come here.

07:24.100 --> 07:25.467
As long as you're
all right, brother.

07:25.500 --> 07:26.567
All right?
- I'm sorry.

07:26.600 --> 07:28.033
- Don't ----ing do that
to me again.

07:28.066 --> 07:30.467
Jeez.
- It's okay.

07:30.500 --> 07:33.033
Sh--.

07:33.066 --> 07:35.033
- All right, let's go ahead
and do the Jet Skis.

07:35.066 --> 07:42.033
♪ ♪

07:49.700 --> 07:51.633
- Bro, it was the scariest
thing I've ever ----ing

07:51.667 --> 07:52.767
gone through in my life.

07:53.000 --> 07:54.033
(BLEEP).

07:54.066 --> 07:55.533
I should never have been

07:55.567 --> 07:57.033
on the water side
of that line.

07:57.066 --> 07:58.700
Um, and I know that.

07:58.734 --> 08:01.000
These are things that I've
been trained not to do.

08:01.033 --> 08:02.767
As I hit the water,
I was fighting

08:03.000 --> 08:05.166
to get my head up to get air.

08:05.200 --> 08:07.400
I realized the line
is gonna not take tension.

08:07.433 --> 08:09.667
It was the most intense force

08:09.700 --> 08:11.600
that I've ever felt
in my life,

08:11.633 --> 08:14.033
the way that that line
tightened around my ankle.

08:14.066 --> 08:16.500
In that moment,
I'd mentally prepared myself

08:16.533 --> 08:18.166
for my foot to be ripped off.

08:18.200 --> 08:20.667
Nobody would have got to me
in time to stop the bleeding,

08:20.700 --> 08:22.533
and I would have just bled-out
in the water.

08:22.567 --> 08:24.700
Brent managed to get those
lines off just in time.

08:24.734 --> 08:27.533
So, I'm--you know,
I owe my life to the guy.

08:27.567 --> 08:28.633
----ing thank God.

08:28.667 --> 08:30.133
- Let's see how you're doing.

08:32.133 --> 08:33.500
Not too bad.

08:33.533 --> 08:35.033
I thought it was gonna
be worse.

08:35.066 --> 08:36.567
- Well, I've had that whole
tender ride

08:36.600 --> 08:38.000
to think how stupid I was.
I mean...

08:38.033 --> 08:40.734
- I would rather focus on
how lucky you were.

08:40.767 --> 08:42.633
- Yeah.
When I was in the tender,

08:42.667 --> 08:44.100
there were times I wanted
to throw up.

08:44.133 --> 08:46.633
There were times
I was almost in tears.

08:46.667 --> 08:48.500
And then there were times
where I was just calm.

08:48.533 --> 08:49.767
- So, we'll just keep it
iced down,

08:50.000 --> 08:51.700
keep it elevated above
your head.

08:51.734 --> 08:53.433
- Thanks, Cap.

08:53.467 --> 08:55.467
Appreciate it.

08:55.500 --> 08:57.000
- For dinner tonight,

08:57.033 --> 08:58.600
I have these beautiful
chicken breasts.

08:58.633 --> 09:00.000
- That chicken looks so good.

09:00.033 --> 09:01.133
- Who ordered chicken?

09:01.166 --> 09:02.567
- Who ordered chicken?

09:02.600 --> 09:03.633
- Chicken is what
poor people eat.

09:03.667 --> 09:05.000
- You're not wrong.

09:05.033 --> 09:06.200
- Chicken's not acceptable.

09:10.166 --> 09:12.000
- Ashton, are you okay?

09:12.633 --> 09:13.333
- I'm fine.
I'm good.

09:13.367 --> 09:14.767
- Oh, my God.

09:15.000 --> 09:17.033
It's swollen.

09:17.066 --> 09:19.166
- But it's good compared to
what it could have been.

09:19.200 --> 09:20.633
- That was scary sh--, man.

09:20.667 --> 09:22.767
- So sca--you thank God.

09:23.000 --> 09:24.266
- Do you usually tow
the tender?

09:24.300 --> 09:25.633
Isn't somebody--
- Yeah.

09:25.667 --> 09:26.734
Yeah, we normally do it.

09:26.767 --> 09:28.767
- Why doesn't someone drive it?

09:29.000 --> 09:30.667
- It's just easier.

09:30.700 --> 09:32.700
- So, someone will--
- Yeah, easier--easier.

09:32.734 --> 09:34.333
- 'Cause a lot
of ----ing corners

09:34.367 --> 09:35.567
are being cut around here.

09:35.600 --> 09:37.233
- It was my fault completely.

09:37.266 --> 09:38.767
Like, I should never have been
on that side of the line.

09:39.000 --> 09:41.667
That's it.

09:41.700 --> 09:43.166
- Cool.
[laughs]

09:43.200 --> 09:44.266
Thanks, buddy.
I appreciate it.

09:44.300 --> 09:45.633
- Yeah, man.
- Chocolate?

09:45.667 --> 09:47.033
- [laughs]
- Not for you.

09:47.066 --> 09:50.033
[upbeat music]

09:50.066 --> 09:52.333
♪ ♪

09:52.367 --> 09:54.200
- Hello.
You want a Jet Ski?

