- I haven't decided if she's
more help than annoying, yet.

10:22.300 --> 10:23.700
- We were talking with Ashton,
she's like,

10:26.367 --> 10:29.100
- She doesn't know what she's
doing enough to be negative.

10:29.133 --> 10:30.166
- Mm-hmm.

10:30.200 --> 10:31.333
- Laura has a lot of opinions.

10:31.367 --> 10:33.700
- Oh, white carpets?
Oh, no.

10:33.734 --> 10:35.367
Who made this bed?

10:35.400 --> 10:37.734
- If Laura had really
ever been a Chief Stew,

10:37.767 --> 10:40.166
she would put herself
in my position

10:40.200 --> 10:43.033
and wouldn't come out
so hot from the start.

10:43.066 --> 10:44.400
- Like, you just arrived.

10:44.433 --> 10:46.033
Wait a second to see
what's going on before...

10:46.066 --> 10:47.734
- Yeah, that's what I'm saying.

10:47.767 --> 10:49.166
- Hi, darling.
How are you?

10:49.200 --> 10:51.233
- I'm ----ing sore,
but it could be worse.

10:51.266 --> 10:52.400
- Do you want me to get you
some dinner?

10:52.433 --> 10:54.000
- That would be amazing.
- Yeah?

10:54.033 --> 10:55.066
- Thanks, man. Thank you.
- Of course.

10:55.100 --> 10:56.633
- I've worked on deck before,

10:56.667 --> 10:59.033
and you do hear all these
horror stories,

10:59.066 --> 11:00.767
and the main thing
that everyone

11:01.000 --> 11:04.000
wants to make sure is that
Ashton is okay.

11:04.033 --> 11:06.266
You know, we just need to look
after him until he gets better.

11:06.300 --> 11:07.767
- Thanks, brother.
I appreciate it.

11:08.000 --> 11:09.066
- No worries.

11:09.100 --> 11:11.100
- Joe, you ready to hop in?

11:11.133 --> 11:14.000
- I'm ready.
- It's a blistering 92.

11:14.033 --> 11:15.767
- Did you want a drink,
as well?

11:16.000 --> 11:17.767
Tequila and grapefruit.
- Thank you so much.

11:18.000 --> 11:19.133
- You're welcome.

11:20.367 --> 11:21.166
I've never really had
a crew member almost die

11:22.433 --> 11:22.633
right in front
of the charter guests.

11:24.000 --> 11:24.100
I think in a situation
like this,

11:24.700 --> 11:25.333
cocktails are the answer.

11:26.433 --> 11:26.700
So, we were just talking
about dinner.

11:27.633 --> 11:28.667
How does 8:30 sound?
- Perfect.

11:28.700 --> 11:30.266
- I'm so glad to be a part
of this.

11:30.300 --> 11:32.033
- Ross.

11:32.066 --> 11:33.433
- Ross, we got the tender
approaching

11:33.467 --> 11:34.767
with the Doc in it.

11:35.000 --> 11:36.700
- Copy.

11:36.734 --> 11:38.200
- I'm Captain Lee.

11:38.233 --> 11:41.033
I'll take you to our patient.
- Okay.

11:41.066 --> 11:42.433
- Ashton.
- How are you?

11:42.467 --> 11:44.133
- Fine, and you?

11:44.166 --> 11:45.467
- I've been better.
- Yeah.

11:45.500 --> 11:47.367
- So, the line wrapped
around here,

11:47.400 --> 11:49.767
pulled tight and crushed.

